1
00:00:03,170 --> 00:00:04,171
(LAUGHING)

2
00:00:07,716 --> 00:00:10,093
There's a strange man
in my bedroom.

3
00:00:10,302 --> 00:00:11,345
No.

4
00:00:11,929 --> 00:00:13,847
-Mum?
-I'm in town.

5
00:00:13,931 --> 00:00:15,891
Look, just go home!
Just go home right now.

6
00:00:16,016 --> 00:00:17,059
Darling, you're breaking up.

7
00:00:17,142 --> 00:00:18,936
-Mum?
-(GLASS BREAKS)

8
00:00:19,228 --> 00:00:20,771
(SCREAMS)

9
00:00:21,396 --> 00:00:23,357
Right, then! I'll be off.

10
00:00:23,982 --> 00:00:27,778
Unless... I don't know.
You could come with me.

11
00:00:28,028 --> 00:00:30,447
-Is it always this dangerous?
-Yeah.

12
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:43,544
(WHOOSHING)

13
00:01:04,356 --> 00:01:06,233
How long have I been gone?

14
00:01:06,316 --> 00:01:07,359
About 12 hours.

15
00:01:07,526 --> 00:01:09,653
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

16
00:01:10,571 --> 00:01:13,240
Oh! Right, I won't be long.
I just want to see my mum.

17
00:01:13,365 --> 00:01:15,284
-What're you gonna tell her?
-I don't know.

18
00:01:15,367 --> 00:01:17,077
I've been to the year
five billion

19
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:19,246
and only been gone,
what, 12 hours?

20
00:01:19,329 --> 00:01:20,414
(CHUCKLES)

21
00:01:20,914 --> 00:01:22,624
No, I'll just tell her
I spent the night at Sharine's.

22
00:01:22,708 --> 00:01:23,834
See you later.

23
00:01:24,209 --> 00:01:26,169
Oh! Don't you disappear.

24
00:01:57,284 --> 00:01:59,995
I'm back! Sharine,
she's all upset again.

25
00:02:00,078 --> 00:02:01,413
Are you in?

26
00:02:01,705 --> 00:02:03,582
So, what's been going on?
How've you been?

27
00:02:03,832 --> 00:02:07,753
What? What's that face for? It's not the first
time I stayed out all night.

28
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:18,263
It's you.

29
00:02:18,847 --> 00:02:20,265
Course it's me.

30
00:02:20,349 --> 00:02:23,935
Oh, my God, it's you.
Oh, my God.

31
00:02:24,645 --> 00:02:25,896
(SOBBING)

32
00:02:33,695 --> 00:02:35,530
It's not 12 hours,
it's 12 months.

33
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:39,743
You've been gone a whole year.
Sorry! (SIGHS)

34
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:45,415
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

35
00:03:21,326 --> 00:03:24,621
JACKIE: The hours I sat here,
days and weeks and months.

36
00:03:24,705 --> 00:03:27,332
All on my own!
I thought you were dead.

37
00:03:27,499 --> 00:03:29,751
And where were you?
Travelling!

38
00:03:29,835 --> 00:03:32,254
What the hell does that mean,
traveling?

39
00:03:32,462 --> 00:03:33,880
That's no sort of answer!

40
00:03:34,548 --> 00:03:36,425
You ask her,
she won't tell me.

41
00:03:36,508 --> 00:03:38,051
That's all she says,
"travelling"”.

42
00:03:38,135 --> 00:03:40,887
-That's what I was doing.
-Well, your passport's still in the drawer.

43
00:03:40,971 --> 00:03:42,848
It's just one lie
after another!

44
00:03:42,931 --> 00:03:47,018
I meant to phone,
I really did. I just... I forgot.

45
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:49,604
What, for a year?
You forgot for a year?

46
00:03:49,688 --> 00:03:51,523
And I'm left sitting here?

47
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:53,191
I just don't believe you!

48
00:03:53,316 --> 00:03:55,777
Why won't you tell me
where you've been?

49
00:03:55,986 --> 00:03:57,070
Actually, it's my fault.

50
00:03:57,154 --> 00:04:00,323
I sort of employed Rose
as my companion.

51
00:04:00,657 --> 00:04:03,493
When you say companion,
is this a sexual relationship?

52
00:04:03,952 --> 00:04:05,203
-No!
-No!

53
00:04:05,328 --> 00:04:06,413
Then what is it?

54
00:04:06,496 --> 00:04:09,499
Because you,
you waltz in here, all charm and smiles,

55
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:12,669
and the next thing I know,
she vanishes off the face of the Earth!

56
00:04:13,044 --> 00:04:15,714
How old are you, then, 40, 457

57
00:04:16,006 --> 00:04:17,466
What, did you find her
on the Internet?

58
00:04:17,549 --> 00:04:19,801
Did you go online
and pretend you're a doctor?

59
00:04:19,885 --> 00:04:22,512
-I am a doctor.
-Prove it. Stitch this, mate.

60
00:04:22,763 --> 00:04:24,973
(GROANS)

61
00:04:26,349 --> 00:04:28,602
Did you think about me at all?

62
00:04:30,437 --> 00:04:33,064
I did, all the time, but...

63
00:04:33,857 --> 00:04:37,027
One phone call.
Just to know that you were alive.

64
00:04:38,653 --> 00:04:42,324
(SNIFFLES)
I'm sorry, I really am.

65
00:04:44,701 --> 00:04:48,371
But do you know
what terrifies me is that you still can't say.

66
00:04:48,955 --> 00:04:50,415
What happened to you, Rose?

67
00:04:50,499 --> 00:04:53,627
What can be so bad
that you can't tell me, sweetheart?

68
00:04:53,710 --> 00:04:55,212
Where were you?

69
00:04:55,545 --> 00:04:56,880
(SNIFFLES)

70
00:05:01,885 --> 00:05:04,095
(SIREN WAILING)

71
00:05:05,388 --> 00:05:07,891
I can't tell her.
I can't even begin.

72
00:05:08,099 --> 00:05:10,310
She's never gonna forgive me.

73
00:05:10,685 --> 00:05:12,813
And I missed a year.
Was it good?

74
00:05:12,896 --> 00:05:15,106
-Middling.
-You're so useless.

75
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:17,484
Well, if it's this much
trouble, are you gonna stay here now?

76
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:19,361
(SIGHS) I don't know.

77
00:05:20,278 --> 00:05:21,696
Can't do that to her again,
though.

78
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:23,573
Well, she's not coming
with us.

79
00:05:23,698 --> 00:05:24,908
(LAUGHS)

80
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:27,953
-No chance!
-I don't do families.

81
00:05:28,036 --> 00:05:29,162
She slapped you!

82
00:05:29,246 --> 00:05:32,374
900 years of time and space, and I've never
been slapped by someone's mother.

83
00:05:32,457 --> 00:05:33,500
Your face.

84
00:05:33,583 --> 00:05:35,836
-It hurt!
-You're so gay!

85
00:05:37,838 --> 00:05:39,756
When you say 900 years...

86
00:05:40,215 --> 00:05:41,258
That's my age.

87
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:43,510
-You're 900 years old.
-Yeah.

88
00:05:45,262 --> 00:05:48,640
My mum was right.
That is one hell of an age gap. (HUFFS)

89
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:51,560
Ugh!

90
00:05:52,769 --> 00:05:55,605
Every conversation
with you just goes mental.

91
00:05:55,856 --> 00:05:57,732
There's no one else
I can talk to.

92
00:05:57,816 --> 00:05:59,442
I've seen all that stuff
up there,

93
00:05:59,526 --> 00:06:02,153
the size of it,
and I can't say a word.

94
00:06:03,321 --> 00:06:05,740
Aliens and spaceships
and things,

95
00:06:05,824 --> 00:06:10,120
and I'm the only person
on planet Earth who knows they exist.

96
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:11,955
(SPACESHIP APPROACHING)

97
00:06:33,435 --> 00:06:34,477
(ELECTRONICS CRACKLING)

98
00:06:46,489 --> 00:06:48,491
(SPACESHIP DESCENDING)

99
00:06:57,083 --> 00:06:58,877
(BELL TOLLS)

100
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,837
(RUMBLING)

101
00:07:15,644 --> 00:07:17,646
Oh, that's just not fair.

102
00:07:18,063 --> 00:07:19,648
(LAUGHS)

103
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:24,027
(SIREN WAILING)

104
00:07:24,194 --> 00:07:26,696
(CAR HORNS HONKING)

105
00:07:26,821 --> 00:07:30,033
WOMAN: All right, all right!
Keep your hair on! It's not my fault, is it?

106
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:31,910
I can't move anywhere!

107
00:07:34,704 --> 00:07:36,081
Ah, just my luck.

108
00:07:36,373 --> 00:07:38,833
Stay back, please.
Back, thank you.

109
00:07:43,338 --> 00:07:44,881
It's blocked off.

110
00:07:44,965 --> 00:07:46,883
(PANTING) We're miles
from the centre.

111
00:07:46,967 --> 00:07:48,843
The city must be gridlocked.

112
00:07:48,927 --> 00:07:50,637
The whole of London
must be closing down.

113
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:53,932
I know, I can't believe
I'm here to see this. This is fantastic.

114
00:07:54,015 --> 00:07:56,226
-Did you know this was going to happen?
-Nope!

115
00:07:56,643 --> 00:07:58,812
-Do you recognise the ship?
-Nope!

116
00:07:58,895 --> 00:08:00,605
-Do you know why it crashed?
-Nope!

117
00:08:00,730 --> 00:08:01,815
Oh, I'm so glad I got you.

118
00:08:01,898 --> 00:08:03,608
I bet you are.
This is what I travel for, Rose,

119
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:05,735
to see history happening
right in front of us.

120
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:08,405
(SIGHS) Well, let's go
and see it.

121
00:08:08,530 --> 00:08:10,448
Never mind the traffic.
We've got the Tardis.

122
00:08:10,573 --> 00:08:11,616
DOCTOR: Hmm, better not.

123
00:08:11,741 --> 00:08:13,368
They've already got
one spaceship in the middle of London.

124
00:08:13,451 --> 00:08:15,578
And I don't wanna shove
another one on top.

125
00:08:15,662 --> 00:08:18,581
Yeah, but yours looks
like a big, blue box. No one's gonna notice.

126
00:08:18,665 --> 00:08:20,250
You'd be surprised,
an emergency like this.

127
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:21,918
There'll be all kinds
of people watching.

128
00:08:22,002 --> 00:08:23,586
Trust me, the Tardis
stays where it is.

129
00:08:25,463 --> 00:08:27,215
So history's happening,
and we're stuck here?

130
00:08:27,298 --> 00:08:28,508
Yes, we are.

131
00:08:31,219 --> 00:08:32,971
We could do
what everybody else does.

132
00:08:35,098 --> 00:08:36,307
We could watch it on TV.

133
00:08:40,270 --> 00:08:44,607
MALE NEWSCASTER: Big Ben destroyed as a
UFO crash-lands in central London.

134
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:47,652
Police reinforcements
are drafted in from across the country

135
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:51,448
to control widespread panic,
looting and civil disturbance.

136
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:54,617
A state of national emergency
has been declared.

137
00:08:54,743 --> 00:08:57,537
Tom Hitchingson
ls at the scene.

138
00:08:57,620 --> 00:08:59,706
The police urge the public
not to panic.

139
00:08:59,789 --> 00:09:01,833
Here's the helpline number
on screen right now,

140
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:04,711
if you're worried
about friends or family.

141
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:09,299
The military
are on the lookout for more spaceships.

142
00:09:09,382 --> 00:09:13,636
Until then, all flights in North American
airspace have been grounded.

143
00:09:14,345 --> 00:09:17,140
The Army are sending
divers into the wreck of the spaceship.

144
00:09:17,974 --> 00:09:19,809
No one knows
what they're going to find.

145
00:09:19,976 --> 00:09:23,063
The President will address the nation
live from the White House,

146
00:09:23,146 --> 00:09:27,150
but the Secretary General
has asked that people watch the skies.

147
00:09:27,484 --> 00:09:29,736
-I've got no choice.
-You've broken your mother's heart.

148
00:09:29,819 --> 00:09:31,446
-Either I make him welcome...
-She's sobbing in my arms.

149
00:09:31,529 --> 00:09:33,990
-...or I risk never seeing you again.
-I cradled her like a child!

150
00:09:34,115 --> 00:09:35,450
Oi! I'm trying to listen!

151
00:09:37,494 --> 00:09:38,703
News is just coming in.

152
00:09:38,787 --> 00:09:41,164
And we can go to Tom
at the Embankment.

153
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:42,999
They've found a body.

154
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:44,793
It's unconfirmed,
but I'm being told

155
00:09:44,876 --> 00:09:47,003
that a body has been found
in the wreckage,

156
00:09:47,087 --> 00:09:49,839
a body
of non-terrestrial origins.

157
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:53,009
It's being brought ashore.

158
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:59,641
A body of some sort has been found
inside the wreckage of a spacecraft.

159
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:02,185
Guess who asked me out?
Billy Croot!

160
00:10:03,186 --> 00:10:07,107
Unconfirmed reports
say the body is of extra-terrestrial origin.

161
00:10:07,857 --> 00:10:11,736
An extraordinary event
unfolding here live in Central London.

162
00:10:11,820 --> 00:10:14,864
The body is being transferred
to a secure unit mortuary.

163
00:10:15,698 --> 00:10:16,950
The whereabouts
as yet unknown.

164
00:10:17,951 --> 00:10:19,327
The roads in Central...

165
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:21,913
And when you
stuff your fins on, you can cover the whole lot

166
00:10:22,122 --> 00:10:24,499
with butter cream.
Oh, look at that!

167
00:10:24,707 --> 00:10:26,918
Then ice it
any colour you want.

168
00:10:27,127 --> 00:10:29,379
And here's one I made
a little bit earlier. And look at that!

169
00:10:30,088 --> 00:10:32,590
Your very own
spaceship, ready to eat.

170
00:10:32,715 --> 00:10:34,384
And for something
a little extra special...

171
00:10:34,509 --> 00:10:36,094
Albion Hospital.

172
00:10:36,427 --> 00:10:38,888
We still don't know
if it's alive or dead.

173
00:10:38,972 --> 00:10:40,974
Whitehall is denying
everything.

174
00:10:41,224 --> 00:10:42,892
But the body has
been brought here.

175
00:10:42,976 --> 00:10:46,146
Albion Hospital. With the roads closed
off, it's the closest to the river.

176
00:10:47,856 --> 00:10:48,857
Go on.

177
00:10:49,983 --> 00:10:53,987
I'm being told that's General
Asquith now entering the hospital.

178
00:10:54,112 --> 00:10:56,573
(SIREN WAILING)

179
00:11:02,245 --> 00:11:06,332
The building's evacuated,
patients moved out onto the streets.

180
00:11:06,583 --> 00:11:10,170
The police still won't confirm
the presence of an alien body

181
00:11:10,253 --> 00:11:12,130
contained inside those walls.

182
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:29,230
Let's have a look, then.

183
00:11:34,611 --> 00:11:35,778
Good God!

184
00:11:38,114 --> 00:11:39,616
And that's real?

185
00:11:39,866 --> 00:11:42,202
It's not a hoax
or a dummy, or...

186
00:11:42,285 --> 00:11:43,828
I've x-rayed the skull.
(SIGHS)

187
00:11:43,912 --> 00:11:47,332
It's wired up
inside like nothing I've ever seen before.

188
00:11:47,457 --> 00:11:49,125
No one could make this up.

189
00:11:51,211 --> 00:11:53,254
We've got experts
being flown in.

190
00:11:53,338 --> 00:11:56,758
Until they arrive,
get that out of sight.

191
00:12:10,021 --> 00:12:11,564
Excuse me, sir.

192
00:12:12,232 --> 00:12:15,235
I know it's a state of emergency and
there's a lot of rumour flying around,

193
00:12:15,318 --> 00:12:17,737
but is it true
what they're saying?

194
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:19,197
About the Prime Minister?

195
00:12:32,043 --> 00:12:34,337
Mystery still surrounds
the whereabouts of the Prime Minister.

196
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:37,090
He's not been seen since
the emergency began.

197
00:12:37,173 --> 00:12:40,426
The opposition are criticising
his lack of leadership...

198
00:12:40,510 --> 00:12:41,719
Hold on.

199
00:12:43,054 --> 00:12:44,889
(CAMERAS CLICKING)

200
00:12:45,515 --> 00:12:49,686
Oh, that's Joseph Green,
MP for Hartley Dale.

201
00:12:49,811 --> 00:12:51,688
He's chairman of the
parliamentary commission

202
00:12:51,771 --> 00:12:55,858
on the monitoring
of sugar standards in exported confectionery.

203
00:12:56,234 --> 00:12:58,861
With respect,
hardly the most important person right now.

204
00:12:59,696 --> 00:13:02,407
Indra Ganesh, sir.
Junior secretary with the MOD.

205
00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:04,534
I'll be your liaison.

206
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:05,827
Where the hell is he?

207
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:08,329
If we could talk in private,
sir? Follow me upstairs.

208
00:13:08,413 --> 00:13:09,706
Excuse me.

209
00:13:09,789 --> 00:13:12,125
Harriet Jones.
MP for Flydale North.

210
00:13:12,208 --> 00:13:13,501
I'm sorry. Can it wait?

211
00:13:13,584 --> 00:13:15,712
But I did have
an appointment at 3:15.

212
00:13:16,045 --> 00:13:18,923
Yes, and then
a spaceship crashed in the middle of London.

213
00:13:19,007 --> 00:13:20,425
Think the schedule
might've changed.

214
00:13:23,469 --> 00:13:24,887
You've heard
about the alien body, sir?

215
00:13:25,054 --> 00:13:27,056
Never mind that. Where is he?

216
00:13:27,181 --> 00:13:28,474
Where's the Prime Minister?

217
00:13:28,558 --> 00:13:30,727
No one knows, sir.
He's disappeared.

218
00:13:30,852 --> 00:13:32,270
I have to inform you that
with the city gridlocked

219
00:13:32,353 --> 00:13:33,563
and the cabinet stranded
outside London,

220
00:13:33,688 --> 00:13:36,774
that makes you
acting Prime Minister with immediate effect.

221
00:13:36,858 --> 00:13:39,319
Oh, Lord! Oh, hold on. (FARTS)

222
00:13:39,402 --> 00:13:40,653
(COUGHS)

223
00:13:40,737 --> 00:13:43,156
Pardon me.
It's a nervous stomach.

224
00:13:43,239 --> 00:13:44,449
Anyway.

225
00:13:49,412 --> 00:13:51,831
Margaret Blaine,
she's with MI5.

226
00:13:51,914 --> 00:13:53,416
There's no more
information, sir.

227
00:13:53,499 --> 00:13:56,502
I personally escorted the Prime Minister
from the cabinet room to his car.

228
00:13:56,627 --> 00:13:59,047
This is Oliver Charles,
transport liaison.

229
00:13:59,255 --> 00:14:01,758
The car's disappeared.
There's no record of it, sir.

230
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:03,426
It literally vanished.

231
00:14:03,676 --> 00:14:06,095
Right. Inside.
Tell me everything.

232
00:14:07,055 --> 00:14:08,264
Er, sir?

233
00:14:09,724 --> 00:14:11,642
The emergency protocols,

234
00:14:11,768 --> 00:14:14,062
detailing the actions
to be taken by the government of Great Britain

235
00:14:14,145 --> 00:14:15,772
in the event
of an alien incursion.

236
00:14:15,897 --> 00:14:17,231
Right. Good!

237
00:14:17,315 --> 00:14:18,566
(FARTS) Blimey!

238
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,526
Pardon me.

239
00:14:21,486 --> 00:14:23,112
Let's work, eh?

240
00:14:43,466 --> 00:14:45,134
(CHUCKLES)

241
00:14:48,137 --> 00:14:51,516
(ALL LAUGHING)

242
00:15:09,117 --> 00:15:10,410
And where do you think
you're going?

243
00:15:10,493 --> 00:15:11,536
Nowhere.

244
00:15:11,702 --> 00:15:13,871
It's just a bit human
in there for me.

245
00:15:14,414 --> 00:15:16,499
History just happened,
and they're talking about where they can buy

246
00:15:16,582 --> 00:15:18,334
dodgy top-up cards
for half price.

247
00:15:19,085 --> 00:15:20,169
I'm off on a wander,
that's all.

248
00:15:20,294 --> 00:15:23,005
Right. There's a spaceship
on the Thames, and you're just wandering.

249
00:15:23,214 --> 00:15:25,216
Nothing to do with me.
It's not an invasion.

250
00:15:25,550 --> 00:15:27,176
That was a genuine
crash-landing.

251
00:15:27,301 --> 00:15:29,887
Angle of descent,
colour of smoke, everything. It was perfect.

252
00:15:30,388 --> 00:15:32,014
-So?
-So, maybe this is it!

253
00:15:32,181 --> 00:15:33,391
First contact.

254
00:15:33,558 --> 00:15:37,061
The day mankind officially
comes into contact with an alien race.

255
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:39,814
I'm not interfering,
'cause you gotta handle this on your own.

256
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:42,316
That's when the human race
finally grows up.

257
00:15:42,859 --> 00:15:45,528
Just this morning
you were tiny and small and made of clay.

258
00:15:45,611 --> 00:15:47,572
Now you can expand! (LAUGHS)

259
00:15:48,531 --> 00:15:50,366
You don't need me.
Go and celebrate history.

260
00:15:50,450 --> 00:15:51,993
Spend some time with your mum.

261
00:15:52,285 --> 00:15:54,495
Promise you won't disappear?

262
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:00,960
Tell you what. Tardis key.

263
00:16:02,086 --> 00:16:04,547
About time you had one.
See you later.

264
00:16:14,307 --> 00:16:15,308
(MUSIC PLAYING)

265
00:16:15,391 --> 00:16:17,393
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

266
00:16:23,191 --> 00:16:26,027
Oi, gorgeous,
come back and join the party!

267
00:16:39,123 --> 00:16:40,333
Oh, my God!

268
00:16:53,179 --> 00:16:55,348
(DEVICE WHIRRS)

269
00:16:56,140 --> 00:16:57,433
(CLICKS)

270
00:16:58,267 --> 00:17:01,687
(MACHINE WHIRRING)

271
00:17:06,484 --> 00:17:08,444
(WHOOSHING)

272
00:17:10,488 --> 00:17:11,864
Oi! Doctor!

273
00:17:12,615 --> 00:17:14,200
Doctor!

274
00:17:33,177 --> 00:17:34,178
(CRACKLES)

275
00:18:06,752 --> 00:18:09,171
I bet no one's
brought you a coffee.

276
00:18:09,255 --> 00:18:11,048
-Thank you.
-Pleasure.

277
00:18:13,009 --> 00:18:14,302
You still can't go in.

278
00:18:14,468 --> 00:18:16,762
Damn, you've seen through
my cunning plan.

279
00:18:16,846 --> 00:18:20,683
Hmm. Look, I'm sorry,
it's just impossible.

280
00:18:21,142 --> 00:18:23,144
Not even for two minutes?

281
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:26,606
I don't get many chances
to walk these corridors,

282
00:18:26,689 --> 00:18:29,233
I'm hardly one of the Babes,
just a faithful backbencher.

283
00:18:29,358 --> 00:18:31,360
And I know we've had
a brave new world

284
00:18:31,444 --> 00:18:33,904
land right on our doorstep,
and that's wonderful.

285
00:18:34,030 --> 00:18:36,490
I think
that's probably wonderful.

286
00:18:37,199 --> 00:18:39,452
Nevertheless, ordinary life
keeps ticking away.

287
00:18:39,535 --> 00:18:43,039
I need to enter this paper.

288
00:18:43,914 --> 00:18:45,750
Oh! Mr Green, sir.

289
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:49,462
I know you're busy, but could you put
this on the next cabinet agenda?

290
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:51,213
-What is it?
-Cottage hospitals.

291
00:18:51,631 --> 00:18:53,090
I've worked out a system

292
00:18:53,215 --> 00:18:57,303
whereby cottage hospitals do not have to be
excluded from Centres of Excellence.

293
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:59,722
You see, my mother's
in the Flydale Infirmary,

294
00:18:59,805 --> 00:19:02,308
that's my constituency,
tiny little place, you wouldn't know it.

295
00:19:02,391 --> 00:19:03,517
But it's given me
a chance to...

296
00:19:03,601 --> 00:19:07,021
By all the saints,
get some perspective, woman!

297
00:19:07,271 --> 00:19:08,522
I'm busy!

298
00:20:23,305 --> 00:20:25,141
(DISTANT THUD ECHOES)

299
00:20:30,730 --> 00:20:32,189
(LOUDER THUD)

300
00:20:34,150 --> 00:20:35,401
(CLICKS)

301
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:37,653
(THUD)

302
00:20:40,322 --> 00:20:41,574
(CLICKS)

303
00:20:43,617 --> 00:20:44,827
(THUD)

304
00:20:51,834 --> 00:20:52,960
(THUD)

305
00:20:54,628 --> 00:20:56,297
(LOUD THUD)

306
00:21:11,020 --> 00:21:14,315
(CONTINUOUS THUDDING)

307
00:21:36,796 --> 00:21:39,799
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

308
00:21:52,061 --> 00:21:53,479
(THUD)

309
00:21:56,273 --> 00:21:58,526
(HEAVY BREATHING BEHIND DOOR)

310
00:21:59,652 --> 00:22:02,738
(LOUD THUDDING)

311
00:22:10,204 --> 00:22:12,665
(SCREAMING)

312
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:15,793
Defence plan Delta!
Come on, move! Move!

313
00:22:27,555 --> 00:22:28,764
It's alive.

314
00:22:28,889 --> 00:22:31,559
Spread out,
tell the perimeter it's a lockdown.

315
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:33,686
Oh, my God, it's still alive!

316
00:22:34,937 --> 00:22:36,105
Do it!

317
00:22:39,525 --> 00:22:41,735
Mick! Terry! Side rooms! Now!

318
00:22:42,862 --> 00:22:43,988
Clear!

319
00:22:45,614 --> 00:22:46,907
Room clear!

320
00:22:46,991 --> 00:22:48,617
-Keep it moving!
-Clear!

321
00:22:51,161 --> 00:22:53,038
I swear, it was dead.
(PANTING)

322
00:22:53,122 --> 00:22:56,041
Coma, shock,
hibernation, anything. What does it look like?

323
00:22:56,458 --> 00:22:58,502
(METALLIC CLANK)

324
00:22:58,586 --> 00:23:00,170
It's still here.

325
00:23:15,728 --> 00:23:17,229
(METAL CLANKS)

326
00:23:33,996 --> 00:23:35,664
(ALIEN GRUNTS)

327
00:23:37,124 --> 00:23:38,208
Hello.

328
00:23:38,334 --> 00:23:41,003
(ALIEN SQUEALS)

329
00:23:41,086 --> 00:23:42,504
Don't shoot!

330
00:23:43,005 --> 00:23:44,882
(ALIEN SQUEALS)

331
00:23:55,768 --> 00:23:57,353
(GUNSHOT)

332
00:23:58,604 --> 00:24:01,440
What did you do that for?
It was scared!

333
00:24:05,361 --> 00:24:06,695
It was scared!

334
00:24:09,365 --> 00:24:10,699
(GRUNTS)

335
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:16,789
GENERAL ASQUITH:
I've got the White House phoning me direct

336
00:24:16,872 --> 00:24:18,999
because Downing Street
won't answer their call!

337
00:24:19,208 --> 00:24:20,334
This is outrageous.

338
00:24:20,417 --> 00:24:23,128
We haven't even started
the vaccination program.

339
00:24:23,754 --> 00:24:24,964
This is appalling.

340
00:24:25,047 --> 00:24:28,092
The nations of the world
are watching the United Kingdom.

341
00:24:28,175 --> 00:24:30,552
GREEN: Well, it has all been
a bit of a shock.

342
00:24:31,095 --> 00:24:34,640
ASQUITH: This is the greatest crisis in
modern history, and you've done nothing.

343
00:24:34,723 --> 00:24:36,642
Your behaviour
has been shameful, sir.

344
00:24:36,725 --> 00:24:39,561
You're supposed
to be in charge. We need positive leadership.

345
00:24:39,687 --> 00:24:41,730
The capital's
ground to a halt.

346
00:24:42,314 --> 00:24:45,150
All the more, we can only assume that
the Prime Minister's disappearance

347
00:24:45,234 --> 00:24:47,945
is the direct result
of hostile alien action.

348
00:24:48,028 --> 00:24:49,738
And what've you been doing?
Nothing!

349
00:24:49,822 --> 00:24:51,573
Sorry! Sorry.

350
00:24:52,282 --> 00:24:55,703
Uh, I thought
I was Prime Minister now.

351
00:24:55,786 --> 00:24:57,204
Only by default!

352
00:24:57,287 --> 00:24:59,665
Oh! That's not fair!

353
00:25:00,124 --> 00:25:02,001
I've been having such fun.

354
00:25:02,418 --> 00:25:03,877
You think this is fun?

355
00:25:03,961 --> 00:25:05,337
It's a hoot, this job.

356
00:25:05,462 --> 00:25:07,464
(LAUGHS) Honestly, it's super!

357
00:25:07,965 --> 00:25:10,801
(FARTS) Oh! Excuse me!

358
00:25:10,884 --> 00:25:14,304
-(FARTING)
-Oh! (LAUGHING)

359
00:25:14,388 --> 00:25:15,556
(FARTING)

360
00:25:15,639 --> 00:25:17,683
-What's going on here?
-(LAUGHING)

361
00:25:17,766 --> 00:25:20,394
And where's the rest of the cabinet? Why
haven't they been airlifted in?

362
00:25:20,477 --> 00:25:23,147
I cancelled it.
They'd only get in the way.

363
00:25:23,230 --> 00:25:27,109
(FARTS) Oops! There I go.
(FARTING)

364
00:25:27,234 --> 00:25:30,029
-Oh! (FARTING)
- (GIGGLING)

365
00:25:30,654 --> 00:25:34,533
I'm shaking my booty. (FARTS)

366
00:25:35,367 --> 00:25:36,452
-Ooh!
-Sir!

367
00:25:36,785 --> 00:25:38,954
Under section five
of the emergency protocols,

368
00:25:39,038 --> 00:25:42,958
it is my duty
to relieve you of command.

369
00:25:43,876 --> 00:25:46,920
And by God, I'll put
this country under martial law if I have to.

370
00:25:47,004 --> 00:25:50,632
-Oh! I'm scared!
-(LAUGHING)

371
00:25:51,050 --> 00:25:54,636
I mean, that's hair-raising.

372
00:25:55,054 --> 00:25:57,306
I mean, literally.

373
00:25:58,432 --> 00:25:59,558
Look!

374
00:26:06,148 --> 00:26:09,485
(LAUGHING)

375
00:26:13,155 --> 00:26:15,407
(LAUGHING)

376
00:26:21,497 --> 00:26:24,249
(SQUELCHY GURGLING)

377
00:26:29,171 --> 00:26:31,465
(MAN SCREAMING)

378
00:26:34,009 --> 00:26:36,804
I just assumed
that's what aliens looked like.

379
00:26:37,012 --> 00:26:39,556
But you're saying
it's an ordinary pig, from Earth.

380
00:26:39,848 --> 00:26:41,016
More like a mermaid.

381
00:26:41,809 --> 00:26:43,769
Victorian showmen
used to draw the crowds

382
00:26:43,852 --> 00:26:45,187
by taking the skull of a cat,

383
00:26:45,312 --> 00:26:48,065
gluing it to a fish
and calling it a mermaid.

384
00:26:48,398 --> 00:26:52,194
Now someone's taken a pig,
opened up its brain, stuck bits on,

385
00:26:52,945 --> 00:26:55,322
then they've
strapped it in that ship, made it dive-bomb.

386
00:26:55,405 --> 00:26:57,366
It must've been terrified.

387
00:26:58,367 --> 00:27:01,411
They've taken this animal
and turned it into a joke.

388
00:27:01,537 --> 00:27:05,541
So it's a fake, a pretend,
like the mermaid.

389
00:27:06,333 --> 00:27:08,710
But the technology
augmenting its brain,

390
00:27:08,794 --> 00:27:10,796
it's like nothing on Earth.

391
00:27:10,879 --> 00:27:12,047
It's alien.

392
00:27:12,339 --> 00:27:14,424
Aliens are faking aliens.

393
00:27:15,217 --> 00:27:17,177
Why would they do that?

394
00:27:18,095 --> 00:27:19,304
Doctor?

395
00:27:25,853 --> 00:27:27,020
Doctor?

396
00:27:27,104 --> 00:27:30,566
(TARDIS WHIRRING)

397
00:27:35,362 --> 00:27:37,030
Here's to the Martians!

398
00:27:37,114 --> 00:27:38,866
ALL: The Martians!

399
00:27:45,455 --> 00:27:47,291
I was gonna come and see you.

400
00:27:47,416 --> 00:27:49,543
Someone owes Mickey
an apology.

401
00:27:50,252 --> 00:27:52,671
-I'm sorry.
-Not you.

402
00:27:53,547 --> 00:27:54,631
Well, it's not my fault.

403
00:27:54,756 --> 00:27:57,342
Be fair,
what was I supposed to think?

404
00:27:59,761 --> 00:28:02,181
You disappear,
who do they turn to? Your boyfriend.

405
00:28:02,264 --> 00:28:04,641
Five times I was taken in
for questioning. Five times.

406
00:28:05,225 --> 00:28:06,810
No evidence. Of course!
There couldn't be, could there?

407
00:28:06,894 --> 00:28:09,021
And then I get her,
your mother,

408
00:28:09,104 --> 00:28:10,856
whispering around the estate,
pointing her finger,

409
00:28:10,939 --> 00:28:13,066
stuff through my letter box,
and all 'cause of you!

410
00:28:13,150 --> 00:28:14,985
Didn't think
I'd be gone so long.

411
00:28:15,068 --> 00:28:16,820
And I waited for you, Rose!

412
00:28:16,945 --> 00:28:19,406
Twelve months. Waited for you
and the Doctor to come back!

413
00:28:19,573 --> 00:28:21,450
Hold on!
You knew about the Doctor?

414
00:28:21,950 --> 00:28:23,452
Why didn't you tell me?

415
00:28:24,119 --> 00:28:26,496
Yeah, yeah.
Why not, Rose? Huh?

416
00:28:26,997 --> 00:28:28,415
How could I tell her
where you went?

417
00:28:28,498 --> 00:28:31,084
-Tell me now.
-I might as well, 'cause you're stuck here.

418
00:28:31,585 --> 00:28:32,669
The Doctor's gone!

419
00:28:33,003 --> 00:28:35,797
Just now, that box thing
just faded away.

420
00:28:36,173 --> 00:28:38,091
-What do you mean?
-He's left you!

421
00:28:38,467 --> 00:28:40,093
Some boyfriend
he turned out to be.

422
00:28:48,101 --> 00:28:49,394
He wouldn't just go.
He promised me.

423
00:28:49,478 --> 00:28:52,147
Oh, he's dumped you, Rose!
Sailed off into space.

424
00:28:52,231 --> 00:28:53,607
How does it feel, huh?

425
00:28:53,690 --> 00:28:56,652
Now, you are left behind with
the rest of us Earthlings.

426
00:28:56,777 --> 00:28:58,570
-Get used to it.
-He would've said.

427
00:28:58,654 --> 00:29:00,656
What are you two chimps
going on about?

428
00:29:01,156 --> 00:29:03,492
What's going on?
What's this Doctor done now?

429
00:29:03,575 --> 00:29:05,244
(LAUGHS MOCKINGLY)
He's vamoosed.

430
00:29:05,327 --> 00:29:07,287
He's not!
'Cause he gave me this.

431
00:29:07,371 --> 00:29:09,164
-(SCOFFS)
-He's not my boyfriend, Mickey.

432
00:29:09,289 --> 00:29:11,917
He's better than that.
He's much more important.

433
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:13,085
And he...

434
00:29:15,504 --> 00:29:18,715
(WARBLING)

435
00:29:18,799 --> 00:29:19,800
(WHOOSHING)

436
00:29:21,593 --> 00:29:22,761
What's that sound?

437
00:29:23,178 --> 00:29:24,888
Mum? Mum, go inside!

438
00:29:24,972 --> 00:29:29,476
Mum, don't stand there!
Just go inside, just... Mum! Oh, blimey.

439
00:29:29,559 --> 00:29:35,065
(LOUD WHIRRING)

440
00:29:35,148 --> 00:29:36,149
(THUDDING)

441
00:29:36,858 --> 00:29:37,985
Huh?

442
00:29:39,278 --> 00:29:41,196
How'd you do that, then?

443
00:29:42,114 --> 00:29:43,699
(DOG BARKING)

444
00:29:46,785 --> 00:29:48,662
All right, so I lied.
I went and had a look.

445
00:29:48,745 --> 00:29:51,373
But the whole crash landing's a fake.
I thought so. Just too perfect.

446
00:29:51,498 --> 00:29:53,292
I mean, hitting Big Ben?
Come on.

447
00:29:53,375 --> 00:29:54,459
So I thought, "Let's go
and have a look..."

448
00:29:54,543 --> 00:29:56,211
-My mum's here.
-(DOOR CREAKS OPEN)

449
00:29:56,712 --> 00:29:59,840
Oh, that's just what I need.
Don't you dare make this place domestic!

450
00:30:00,299 --> 00:30:03,468
You ruined my life, Doctor.
They thought she was dead.

451
00:30:03,552 --> 00:30:04,970
I was a murder suspect
because of you.

452
00:30:05,595 --> 00:30:07,055
See what I mean? Domestic!

453
00:30:07,472 --> 00:30:08,974
I bet you don't even
remember my name!

454
00:30:09,057 --> 00:30:10,309
-Ricky.
-It's Mickey.

455
00:30:10,392 --> 00:30:12,227
-No, it's Ricky.
-I think I know my own name.

456
00:30:12,311 --> 00:30:13,979
You think you know
your own name? How stupid are you?

457
00:30:14,062 --> 00:30:16,023
Mum, don't! Don't go anywhere!

458
00:30:16,106 --> 00:30:17,482
Don't start a fight.

459
00:30:18,942 --> 00:30:21,403
Mum! It's not like that,
he's not...

460
00:30:22,779 --> 00:30:25,073
I'll... I'll be up
in @ minute! Hold on!

461
00:30:26,825 --> 00:30:28,160
That was a real spaceship?

462
00:30:28,243 --> 00:30:30,370
-Yep!
-So it was all a pack of lies.

463
00:30:30,454 --> 00:30:32,581
What is it, then,
that they're invading?

464
00:30:32,998 --> 00:30:35,917
Funny way to invade,
putting the world on red alert.

465
00:30:36,043 --> 00:30:37,919
Good point!
So, what're they up to?

466
00:30:42,049 --> 00:30:43,425
FEMALE NEWS REPORTER:
As the crisis continues

467
00:30:43,508 --> 00:30:46,094
and the government
shows a remarkable lack of leadership,

468
00:30:46,178 --> 00:30:48,013
paranoia sweeps the country.

469
00:30:48,096 --> 00:30:50,599
There've been at least three
reports of public assaults

470
00:30:50,891 --> 00:30:53,518
on people possibly
identified as aliens.

471
00:30:53,602 --> 00:30:55,687
Now back to Tom Hitchingson.

472
00:30:56,021 --> 00:30:58,231
TOM: Are there
more ships to come?

473
00:30:58,440 --> 00:31:00,442
And what is their intention?

474
00:31:01,318 --> 00:31:04,279
The authorities
are now asking, if anyone knows anything,

475
00:31:04,738 --> 00:31:08,617
if any previous sighting has been
made, then call this number.

476
00:31:09,117 --> 00:31:10,827
We need your help.

477
00:31:10,952 --> 00:31:13,789
(DIALLING)

478
00:31:15,248 --> 00:31:16,750
(ENGAGED TONE DRONING)

479
00:31:17,793 --> 00:31:18,794
(SPEED-DIALLING)

480
00:31:18,877 --> 00:31:20,379
(ENGAGED TONE DRONING)

481
00:31:21,129 --> 00:31:22,255
(SPEED-DIALLING)

482
00:31:23,298 --> 00:31:26,968
Yes! I've seen one,
I really have, an alien. And she's with him.

483
00:31:27,094 --> 00:31:31,473
My daughter, she's with him, and she's not
safe. Oh, my God, she's not safe.

484
00:31:31,556 --> 00:31:33,558
(SIGHS)

485
00:31:33,642 --> 00:31:37,229
I've seen an alien,
and I know his name. He's called the Doctor.

486
00:31:37,562 --> 00:31:42,692
It's a box, a blue box.
She called it a Tardis.

487
00:31:43,985 --> 00:31:49,991
(ALARM BLARING)

488
00:31:57,833 --> 00:31:59,000
So what you doing down there?

489
00:31:59,126 --> 00:32:00,544
-Ricky.
-Mickey.

490
00:32:01,545 --> 00:32:02,712
Ricky.

491
00:32:03,296 --> 00:32:05,257
If I was to tell you
what I was doing to the controls

492
00:32:05,340 --> 00:32:07,592
of my frankly magnificent
time ship,

493
00:32:07,676 --> 00:32:09,469
would you even
begin to understand?

494
00:32:10,470 --> 00:32:12,806
-I suppose not...
-Well, shut it, then.

495
00:32:19,729 --> 00:32:21,898
-Some friend you've got.
-He's winding you up.

496
00:32:25,110 --> 00:32:26,445
I am sorry.

497
00:32:26,528 --> 00:32:28,321
-Okay.
-I am, though.

498
00:32:34,286 --> 00:32:36,037
Every day, I looked.

499
00:32:37,205 --> 00:32:38,832
On every street corner,
wherever I went,

500
00:32:38,915 --> 00:32:41,376
looking for a blue box
for a whole year.

501
00:32:41,710 --> 00:32:43,837
It's only been
a few days for me.

502
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:47,340
I don't know.
It's hard to tell inside this thing.

503
00:32:47,424 --> 00:32:50,427
But I swear,
it's just a few days since I left you.

504
00:32:53,555 --> 00:32:55,307
Not enough time
to miss me, then.

505
00:32:56,099 --> 00:32:57,601
I did miss you.

506
00:33:03,482 --> 00:33:04,900
I missed you.

507
00:33:07,068 --> 00:33:10,864
So, um, in 12 months...

508
00:33:11,948 --> 00:33:13,158
Have you been seeing
anyone else?

509
00:33:13,241 --> 00:33:14,367
Nope.

510
00:33:15,410 --> 00:33:16,495
Okay.

511
00:33:16,578 --> 00:33:18,747
Mainly 'cause everyone
thinks I murdered you.

512
00:33:19,581 --> 00:33:20,582
Right.

513
00:33:24,961 --> 00:33:27,172
So, now that you've come back,

514
00:33:29,382 --> 00:33:30,717
are you gonna stay?

515
00:33:33,303 --> 00:33:34,888
-(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)
-Got it! Ha-ha!

516
00:33:34,971 --> 00:33:36,014
(MACHINE POWERING UP)

517
00:33:36,097 --> 00:33:38,475
Patched in the radar,
looped it back 12 hours,

518
00:33:38,558 --> 00:33:40,685
so it'll follow
the flight of that spaceship. Here we go.

519
00:33:40,769 --> 00:33:42,187
- (CLICKS)
-Hold on.

520
00:33:42,896 --> 00:33:43,939
Come on!

521
00:33:44,356 --> 00:33:46,441
-(BEEPING)
-That's the spaceship on its way to Earth.

522
00:33:47,150 --> 00:33:48,151
See?

523
00:33:48,276 --> 00:33:49,903
Except... Hold on.

524
00:33:51,154 --> 00:33:52,739
See? The spaceship
did a slingshot

525
00:33:52,822 --> 00:33:54,199
round the Earth
before it landed.

526
00:33:54,282 --> 00:33:56,826
-ROSE: What does that mean?
-Means it came from Earth in the first place.

527
00:33:56,910 --> 00:33:58,620
It went up and came back down.

528
00:33:58,703 --> 00:34:01,706
Whoever those aliens are, they haven't just
arrived. They've been here for a while.

529
00:34:01,790 --> 00:34:04,584
Question is,
what've they been doing?

530
00:34:11,174 --> 00:34:13,468
What do you think?
How's the compression?

531
00:34:13,593 --> 00:34:16,388
I think I've got too much
ballast round the middle.

532
00:34:17,597 --> 00:34:19,266
(FARTS) Ooh, that's better!

533
00:34:19,349 --> 00:34:21,893
We've really got to fix
the gas exchange. It's getting ridiculous.

534
00:34:21,977 --> 00:34:24,104
I don't know. Seems
very human to me.

535
00:34:24,187 --> 00:34:26,022
Uh, better get rid
of his skin!

536
00:34:26,940 --> 00:34:30,235
Shame,
I quite enjoyed being Oliver.

537
00:34:31,027 --> 00:34:33,989
He had a wife,
a mistress and a young farmer.

538
00:34:37,659 --> 00:34:39,286
God, I was busy.

539
00:34:41,329 --> 00:34:42,664
Back to work!

540
00:34:42,747 --> 00:34:44,291
I have an army to command!

541
00:34:44,374 --> 00:34:47,294
MARGARET: Careful now.
We're not there yet.

542
00:34:54,384 --> 00:34:56,928
General Asquith! Sir,
we've had a priority alarm.

543
00:34:57,012 --> 00:34:58,722
It's Code Nine,
confirmed Code Nine.

544
00:35:00,015 --> 00:35:05,687
Right. Good. Code Nine, huh?
Which would mean?

545
00:35:07,188 --> 00:35:09,983
In the event
of the emergency protocols being activated,

546
00:35:10,066 --> 00:35:11,776
we've got software
which automatically searches

547
00:35:11,860 --> 00:35:13,695
all communications
for keywords.

548
00:35:13,778 --> 00:35:15,363
And one of those words
is "Doctor".

549
00:35:15,864 --> 00:35:17,324
I think we've found him, sir.

550
00:35:17,407 --> 00:35:19,743
What sort of doctor?
Who is he?

551
00:35:20,035 --> 00:35:22,412
Well, evidently, he's some sort of
expert in extraterrestrial affairs.

552
00:35:22,537 --> 00:35:25,290
The ultimate expert!
And we need him, sir.

553
00:35:25,373 --> 00:35:27,417
We need him here right now.

554
00:35:28,543 --> 00:35:29,544
(SHOUTING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

555
00:35:29,753 --> 00:35:31,296
-(PEOPLE CLAMOURING)
-(SIRENS BLARING)

556
00:35:31,379 --> 00:35:33,298
(WOMAN CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY ON TV)

557
00:35:33,882 --> 00:35:36,426
-How many channels you get?
-All the basic packages.

558
00:35:36,676 --> 00:35:39,095
-You get sports channels?
-Yes, I get the football.

559
00:35:39,179 --> 00:35:40,388
Hold on. I know that lot.

560
00:35:40,472 --> 00:35:41,640
FEMALE REPORTER:
...but it's looking likely

561
00:35:41,723 --> 00:35:44,559
that the government's
bringing in alien specialists,

562
00:35:44,643 --> 00:35:48,396
those people who've
devoted their lives to studying outer space.

563
00:35:49,189 --> 00:35:52,734
UNIT! United Nations
Intelligence Taskforce. Good people.

564
00:35:53,026 --> 00:35:54,361
How do you know them?

565
00:35:54,444 --> 00:35:56,279
'Cause he's worked for them.

566
00:35:56,404 --> 00:35:58,907
Oh, yeah. Don't think
I sat on my backside for 12 months, Doctor.

567
00:35:58,990 --> 00:36:00,241
I read up on you!

568
00:36:00,367 --> 00:36:02,535
You look deep enough
on the Internet or in the history books,

569
00:36:02,619 --> 00:36:03,745
and there's his name.

570
00:36:03,828 --> 00:36:04,996
Followed by
a list of the dead.

571
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:06,623
That's nice. Good boy, Ricky.

572
00:36:06,748 --> 00:36:08,541
If you know them,
why don't you go and help?

573
00:36:08,625 --> 00:36:11,211
They wouldn't recognise me.
I've changed a lot since the old days.

574
00:36:11,878 --> 00:36:14,172
Besides, the world's
on a knife edge.

575
00:36:14,297 --> 00:36:15,340
There's aliens out there,

576
00:36:15,423 --> 00:36:18,093
and fake aliens
wanna keep this alien out of the mix.

577
00:36:18,426 --> 00:36:20,261
-I'm going undercover.
-(DINGING)

578
00:36:20,387 --> 00:36:22,681
And, uh, better keep
the Tardis out of sight. Ricky!

579
00:36:22,972 --> 00:36:24,974
You've got a car.
You can do some driving.

580
00:36:25,100 --> 00:36:26,184
Where to?

581
00:36:26,267 --> 00:36:28,436
The roads are clearing.
Let's go and have a look at that spaceship.

582
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:30,313
(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)

583
00:36:30,980 --> 00:36:33,775
MAN ON MEGAPHONE: Do not move!
Step away from the box!

584
00:36:33,858 --> 00:36:36,611
-Raise your hands above your head!
-(SIRENS WAILING)

585
00:36:45,286 --> 00:36:47,122
(POLICE SHOUTING)

586
00:36:51,668 --> 00:36:52,794
Rose!

587
00:36:54,921 --> 00:36:57,006
Rose! Rose!

588
00:37:06,141 --> 00:37:07,267
Take me to your leader!

589
00:37:07,350 --> 00:37:09,060
JACKIE: My daughter!

590
00:37:09,269 --> 00:37:10,895
(CHATTERING OVER POLICE RADIO)

591
00:37:13,940 --> 00:37:15,442
This is a bit posh.

592
00:37:15,525 --> 00:37:18,695
If I knew it was gonna be like this, being
arrested, I would've done it years ago.

593
00:37:18,778 --> 00:37:20,947
We're not being arrested,
we're being escorted.

594
00:37:21,656 --> 00:37:23,658
-Where to?
-Where do you think?

595
00:37:23,825 --> 00:37:25,744
Downing Street. (LAUGHS)

596
00:37:26,161 --> 00:37:28,663
-You're kidding!
-I'm not! (LAUGHS)

597
00:37:28,747 --> 00:37:31,207
-10 Downing Street?
-That's the one!

598
00:37:31,624 --> 00:37:34,627
Oh, my God! I'm going
to 10 Downing Street?

599
00:37:35,378 --> 00:37:37,422
-How come?
-I hate to say it, but Mickey was right.

600
00:37:37,505 --> 00:37:40,133
Over the years, I've visited
this planet a lot of times, and I've been, uh,

601
00:37:40,383 --> 00:37:41,551
noticed.

602
00:37:42,135 --> 00:37:43,219
Now they need you.

603
00:37:43,344 --> 00:37:46,139
Like it said on the news,
they're gathering experts in alien knowledge.

604
00:37:46,222 --> 00:37:48,224
And who's
the biggest expert of the lot?

605
00:37:49,350 --> 00:37:51,269
-Patrick Moore?
-Apart from him.

606
00:37:51,853 --> 00:37:53,772
Oh, don't you just love it.

607
00:37:53,855 --> 00:37:57,192
Oh, I'm telling you, Lloyd George, oh, he used
to drink me under the table.

608
00:37:57,484 --> 00:37:58,568
Who's the Prime Minister now?

609
00:37:58,693 --> 00:38:01,112
How should I know?
I missed a year.

610
00:38:02,530 --> 00:38:05,742
(SIREN WAILING)

611
00:38:10,955 --> 00:38:13,792
(REPORTERS CLAMOURING)

612
00:38:24,093 --> 00:38:25,470
Oh, my God!

613
00:38:28,389 --> 00:38:31,059
So she's all right, then?
She's not in any trouble?

614
00:38:31,184 --> 00:38:33,645
All I can say
is that your daughter and her companion

615
00:38:33,728 --> 00:38:35,980
might be in a position
to help the country. (SIGHS)

616
00:38:36,064 --> 00:38:38,399
We'll need to know
how she made contact with this man,

617
00:38:38,483 --> 00:38:40,068
if he is a man.

618
00:38:40,485 --> 00:38:42,320
(STOMACH RUMBLES) Ooh!

619
00:38:43,238 --> 00:38:44,614
Right, off you go, then.

620
00:38:44,739 --> 00:38:47,408
I need to talk with Mrs Tyler
on my own, thank you.

621
00:38:47,492 --> 00:38:48,493
(STOMACH GURGLING)

622
00:38:56,042 --> 00:38:57,752
(INDISTINCT)

623
00:38:58,378 --> 00:39:00,463
Harriet Jones,
MP, Flydale North.

624
00:39:10,849 --> 00:39:13,935
Ladies and gentlemen,
can we convene? Quick as we can, please.

625
00:39:14,018 --> 00:39:15,520
It's this way on the right,
and can I remind you

626
00:39:15,603 --> 00:39:18,106
ID cards
are to be worn at all times.

627
00:39:19,232 --> 00:39:20,692
Here's your ID card.

628
00:39:20,775 --> 00:39:22,610
I'm sorry. Your companion
doesn't have clearance.

629
00:39:22,735 --> 00:39:23,820
I don't go anywhere
without her.

630
00:39:23,945 --> 00:39:27,282
You're the Code Nine, not her.
I'm sorry, Doctor.

631
00:39:28,032 --> 00:39:29,158
It's, uh, Doctor, isn't it?

632
00:39:29,784 --> 00:39:31,828
-She'll have to stay outside.
-She's staying with me.

633
00:39:31,911 --> 00:39:34,163
Look, even I don't have
clearance to go in there.

634
00:39:34,414 --> 00:39:35,957
I can't let her in
and that's a fact.

635
00:39:36,082 --> 00:39:37,125
That's all right. You go.

636
00:39:37,208 --> 00:39:38,960
Excuse me. Are you the Doctor?

637
00:39:39,085 --> 00:39:41,337
-Sure?
-Not now. We're busy. Can't you go home?

638
00:39:41,421 --> 00:39:43,172
I just need a word,
in private!

639
00:39:43,256 --> 00:39:44,966
You haven't got clearance.
Now leave it!

640
00:39:45,049 --> 00:39:47,302
I'm gonna have to
leave you with security.

641
00:39:47,427 --> 00:39:51,055
It's all right,
I'll look after her. Let me be of some use.

642
00:39:53,308 --> 00:39:55,685
Walk with me.
Just keep walking.

643
00:39:56,519 --> 00:39:58,813
That's right,
don't look round.

644
00:39:59,898 --> 00:40:02,191
Harriet Jones.
MP, Flydale North.

645
00:40:23,713 --> 00:40:28,343
This friend of yours,
he's an expert, is that right?

646
00:40:29,552 --> 00:40:31,846
He knows about aliens?

647
00:40:31,930 --> 00:40:34,432
-Why do you wanna to know?
-(SOBBING)

648
00:40:35,516 --> 00:40:38,353
(CRYING)

649
00:40:42,357 --> 00:40:44,609
Ladies and gentlemen,
if I could have your attention, please.

650
00:40:44,692 --> 00:40:46,778
As you can see
from the summaries in front of you,

651
00:40:46,861 --> 00:40:48,988
the ship had
one porcine pilot.

652
00:40:49,072 --> 00:40:51,908
Of course, the really interesting
bit happened three days ago, see?

653
00:40:51,991 --> 00:40:53,826
Filed away
under any other business,

654
00:40:53,910 --> 00:40:56,955
the North Sea satellite
detected a signal,

655
00:40:57,038 --> 00:40:59,749
a little blip of radiation
at 100 fathoms.

656
00:40:59,874 --> 00:41:01,542
Like there's
something down there.

657
00:41:01,626 --> 00:41:02,919
You were just about
to investigate,

658
00:41:03,002 --> 00:41:04,379
and next thing you know,
this happens.

659
00:41:04,462 --> 00:41:07,548
Spaceships. Pigs.
Massive diversion. From what?

660
00:41:08,257 --> 00:41:12,387
They turn the body
into a suit, a disguise for the thing inside!

661
00:41:12,470 --> 00:41:15,139
It's all right, I believe you.

662
00:41:15,598 --> 00:41:17,767
It's... It's alien.

663
00:41:18,559 --> 00:41:21,604
They must have some serious
technology behind this.

664
00:41:21,688 --> 00:41:23,356
If we could find it,

665
00:41:23,773 --> 00:41:25,400
we could use it.

666
00:41:25,483 --> 00:41:26,484
Ooh!

667
00:41:27,860 --> 00:41:29,195
Oh, my God. Is that...

668
00:41:29,278 --> 00:41:31,280
Harriet, for God's sake!
This has gone beyond a joke.

669
00:41:31,406 --> 00:41:32,573
You cannot just wander...

670
00:41:34,867 --> 00:41:36,077
Oh, my God.

671
00:41:37,453 --> 00:41:38,788
That's the Prime Minister.

672
00:41:39,497 --> 00:41:42,875
If aliens fake an alien crash
and an alien pilot, what do they get?

673
00:41:46,587 --> 00:41:47,755
Us.

674
00:41:48,589 --> 00:41:50,008
They get us.

675
00:41:50,758 --> 00:41:53,177
It's not a diversion,
it's a trap.

676
00:41:53,761 --> 00:41:54,929
Oh!

677
00:41:57,598 --> 00:41:59,600
Has someone been naughty?

678
00:42:06,107 --> 00:42:07,859
It was bigger on the inside.

679
00:42:07,942 --> 00:42:10,820
I don't know. What do I know
about spaceships?

680
00:42:10,945 --> 00:42:14,949
That's what worries me.
You see, this man is classified as trouble,

681
00:42:15,074 --> 00:42:18,786
which means
that anyone associated with him is trouble.

682
00:42:20,163 --> 00:42:21,831
And that's my job.

683
00:42:23,041 --> 00:42:24,792
Eliminating trouble.

684
00:42:26,961 --> 00:42:29,213
(BUZZING)

685
00:42:29,881 --> 00:42:34,218
INDRA: But that's not possible.
He left this afternoon.

686
00:42:35,178 --> 00:42:37,805
The Prime Minister
left Downing Street. He was driven away!

687
00:42:38,473 --> 00:42:40,683
And who told you that?

688
00:42:42,810 --> 00:42:43,853
Hmm?

689
00:42:46,355 --> 00:42:47,482
Me!

690
00:42:51,652 --> 00:42:53,946
This is all about us.
Alien experts.

691
00:42:54,030 --> 00:42:55,740
The only people
with the knowledge how to find them

692
00:42:55,823 --> 00:42:57,283
gathered together in one room.

693
00:42:57,408 --> 00:42:58,868
(FARTING)

694
00:43:00,661 --> 00:43:03,289
Excuse me. Do you mind not
farting while I'm saving the world?

695
00:43:03,623 --> 00:43:06,250
Would you rather
silent but deadly?

696
00:43:14,092 --> 00:43:16,177
(JOSEPH LAUGHING)

697
00:43:43,621 --> 00:43:46,040
(GASPS) Ah!

698
00:43:48,709 --> 00:43:50,128
(SQUELCHING)

699
00:43:59,720 --> 00:44:02,140
(GROANING)

700
00:44:06,561 --> 00:44:08,688
(GROWLING)

701
00:44:08,813 --> 00:44:10,523
(CHUCKLING)

702
00:44:10,606 --> 00:44:14,652
(GROWLING)

703
00:44:14,861 --> 00:44:19,574
-(SNARLING)
-(CONTINUES LAUGHING)

704
00:44:27,415 --> 00:44:29,167
(GROWLING)

705
00:44:42,930 --> 00:44:44,807
We are the Slitheen.

706
00:44:45,766 --> 00:44:47,894
(LAUGHING IN ALIEN VOICE)

707
00:44:47,977 --> 00:44:49,604
(GROWLS)

708
00:44:50,146 --> 00:44:51,772
(INDRA SCREAMING)

709
00:44:54,775 --> 00:44:56,903
-(SCREAMS)
-(GROWLING)

710
00:45:03,201 --> 00:45:05,870
Thank you all
for wearing your ID cards.

711
00:45:07,538 --> 00:45:09,957
They'll help
to identify the bodies.

712
00:45:10,082 --> 00:45:13,044
-(BUZZING)
-(GROANING)

713
00:45:18,966 --> 00:45:21,177
(SCREAMING IN TERROR)

714
00:45:23,221 --> 00:45:24,555
(SCREAMING)

715
00:45:24,639 --> 00:45:27,975
(ALIEN LAUGHS)

716
00:45:35,608 --> 00:45:38,819
Yesterday saw the start
of a brave new world.

717
00:45:40,071 --> 00:45:41,739
Today might see it end.

718
00:45:42,156 --> 00:45:44,742
Right! You want aliens, you've got
them. They're inside Downing Street.

719
00:45:44,825 --> 00:45:45,826
Come on!

720
00:45:46,118 --> 00:45:48,329
(SCREAMING)

721
00:45:50,873 --> 00:45:52,291
(BOTH EXCLAIMING)

722
00:45:52,833 --> 00:45:54,835
Planet Earth is at war.

723
00:45:59,882 --> 00:46:01,092
Everybody run!

724
00:46:03,177 --> 00:46:05,179
-Who exactly are the Slitheen?
-They're aliens.

725
00:46:07,682 --> 00:46:09,433
I could save the world
but lose you.

726
00:46:13,145 --> 00:46:14,689
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

